Andropogoneae Species

Michelle C. Stitzer

Themeda triandra

Photo by Richard Gill, licensed under CC-BY-NC 4.0

The assembly is allelic, and the genome is diploid. It has a haploid genome size of 700 Mb, and has 10 haploid chromosomes.

Metaphase chromosomes of Themeda triandraroot tips, scale bar 10 m

Species herbarium records

Herbarium records of Themeda triandra from AuBuchon-Elder et al 2022 are plotted with black points, The sampled individual this genome was generated from is shown in a colored point. The green background shows the biogeographic ranges of all Andropogoneae species in AuBuchon-Elder et al 2022.

Figure 1 from the main text, with Themeda triandra highlighted with colored points.

Highlighted Figure 2

Figure 2 from the main text, with Themeda triandra highlighted with colored points.

Dotplot of Themeda triandra vs.Paspalum vaginatum.

Like dotplots shown in Figure 3 of the main text, this shows syntenic blocks in Themeda triandra along the y-axis, vs P. vaginatum on the x-axis. As Themeda triandra is a diploid with an allelic, assembly, we expect 2 paths for any x-axis position.

Fractionation of Themeda triandra

Like plots shown in Figure 4 of the main text, this shows proportion of retained genes in Themeda triandra along the y-axis, vs P. vaginatum chromosomes on the x-axis. As Themeda triandra is a diploid with an allelic, assembly, we expect 2 lines, two for each subgenome.
